def: In a naked manner; without covering or disguise; manifestly;simply; barely.
A composite herb (Cichorium Endivia). Its finely divided andmuch curled leaves, when blanched, are used for salad. Wild endive(Bot.), chicory or succory.
To tear up by the roots; to eradicate; to uproot.
Causing bewilderment or great perplexity; as, bewilderingdifficulties.-- Be*wil"der*ing*ly, adv.
An elementary substance, resembling a metal in its appearanceand physical properties, but in its chemical relations belonging tothe class of nonmetallic substances. Atomic weight, 120. Symbol, Sb.
Any one of several species of Asiatic cuckoos of the genusTaccocua, as the Bengal sirkeer (T. sirkee).
As much as a pocket will hold; enough to fill a pocket; as,pocketfuls of chestnuts.
Implying, or partaking of the nature of, fatalism.
Composed of superposed branches in such a way as to imitate asimple axis; as, a sympodial stem.
To whirl round, or revolve, with a whizzing noise; to fly ormore quickly with a buzzing or whizzing sound; to whiz.The partridge bursts away on whirring wings. Beattie.
The discharge of the menses; also, the state or the period ofmenstruating.
